/-! ## Project-local Mathlib supplement ‚Äî `jShriekOU` transport along a scheme iso (Need #1)

The corepresenting object `jShriekOU V` of `Œì(V,-)` is carried along a scheme isomorphism
`œÜ : X ‚âÖ Y` by the induced pushforward equivalence: `Œ¶.functor (jShriekOU V) ‚âÖ jShriekOU (œÜ.inv‚Åª¬πV)`.
The argument is pure corepresentability transport ‚Äî `jShriekOU V` is never unfolded.  Both sides
corepresent the *same* `Type`-valued sections functor `Œì(œÜ.inv‚Åª¬πV,-)`: the right side directly (the
additive corepresentability `jShriekOU_homEquiv`), the left side via the pushforward adjunction
(`Œ¶.functor ‚ä£ Œ¶.inverse`) composed with the definitional identity "sections of a pushforward =
sections over the preimage open".  `CorepresentableBy.uniqueUpToIso` then produces the iso. -/

/-- **`jShriekOU V` corepresents the `Type`-valued sections functor `Œì(V,-)`.**  Repackages the
additive corepresentability `jShriekOU_homEquiv` as a `CorepresentableBy` of `sectionsFunctor V`
post-composed with the forgetful functor to types. Project-local. -/
private noncomputable def sectionsCorep {X : Scheme.{u}} (V : TopologicalSpace.Opens X) :
    (sectionsFunctor V ‚ãô forget AddCommGrpCat).CorepresentableBy (jShriekOU V) where
  homEquiv {B} := (jShriekOU_homEquiv V B).toEquiv
  homEquiv_comp g f := jShriekOU_homEquiv_nat V f g

/-- **The pushforward of `jShriekOU V` corepresents `Œì(œÜ.inv‚Åª¬πV,-)`.**  Via the pushforward
adjunction `Œ¶.functor ‚ä£ Œ¶.inverse` and the definitional identity "sections of `œÜ.inv`-pushforward
over `V` = sections over `œÜ.inv‚Åª¬πV`", the object `Œ¶.functor (jShriekOU V)` corepresents the same
`Type`-valued sections functor as `jShriekOU (œÜ.inv‚Åª¬πV)`.  Project-local. -/
private noncomputable def sectionsCorepPushforward {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (œÜ : X ‚âÖ Y)
    (V : TopologicalSpace.Opens X) :
    (sectionsFunctor (œÜ.inv ‚Åª¬π·µÅ V) ‚ãô forget AddCommGrpCat).CorepresentableBy
      ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso œÜ).functor.obj (jShriekOU V)) where
  homEquiv {B} :=
    ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso œÜ).toAdjunction.homEquiv (jShriekOU V) B).trans
      (jShriekOU_homEquiv V ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso œÜ).inverse.obj B)).toEquiv
  homEquiv_comp {B B'} g f := by
    simp only [Equiv.trans_apply]
    rw [(Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso œÜ).toAdjunction.homEquiv_naturality_right]
    erw [jShriekOU_homEquiv_nat V
      ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso œÜ).toAdjunction.homEquiv (jShriekOU V) B f)
      ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso œÜ).inverse.map g)]

/-- **A scheme isomorphism carries `jShriekOU` along** (blueprint `lem:jshriek_transport_along_iso`).
For `œÜ : X ‚âÖ Y` and an open `V ‚äÜ X`, the pushforward equivalence sends the corepresenting object of
`Œì(V,-)` to that of `Œì(œÜ.inv‚Åª¬πV,-)`:
`Œ¶.functor (jShriekOU V) ‚âÖ jShriekOU (œÜ.inv‚Åª¬πV)`.  Project-local: the geometric naturality of `j_!`
under a scheme iso (the first-`Ext`-argument transport of Need #1). -/
noncomputable def jShriekOU_transport_along_iso {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (œÜ : X ‚âÖ Y)
    (V : TopologicalSpace.Opens X) :
    (Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso œÜ).functor.obj (jShriekOU V) ‚âÖ
      jShriekOU (œÜ.inv ‚Åª¬π·µÅ V) :=
  (sectionsCorepPushforward œÜ V).uniqueUpToIso (sectionsCorep (œÜ.inv ‚Åª¬π·µÅ V))

/-! ## Project-local Mathlib supplement ‚Äî quasi-coherence transport along a scheme iso (`hqc`) -/

/-- **A scheme isomorphism transports an open cover.** If a family `Z` of opens covers `X`
(in the sense of the opens Grothendieck topology, i.e. `CoversTop`), then the preimage family
`œÜ.inv ‚Åª¬π·µÅ (Z i)` covers `Y`.  Project-local: the cover-transport half of
`pushforward_iso_preserves_qcoh` (Need #1 `hqc`). -/
private lemma coversTop_preimage_of_iso {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (œÜ : X ‚âÖ Y) {I : Type*}
    (Z : I ‚Üí X.Opens) (hZ : (Opens.grothendieckTopology X).CoversTop Z) :
    (Opens.grothendieckTopology Y).CoversTop (fun i => œÜ.inv ‚Åª¬π·µÅ Z i) := by
  intro W x hx
  obtain ‚ü®U', f, hf, hU'‚ü© := hZ ‚ä§ (œÜ.inv.base x) (by trivial)
  obtain ‚ü®i, ‚ü®g‚ü©‚ü© := hf
  have hxZ : œÜ.inv.base x ‚àà Z i := (leOfHom g) hU'
  refine ‚ü®W ‚äì (œÜ.inv ‚Åª¬π·µÅ Z i), homOfLE inf_le_left,
    ‚ü®i, ‚ü®homOfLE inf_le_right‚ü©‚ü©, ‚ü®hx, ?_‚ü©‚ü©
  exact hxZ

