/-! ## Project-local Mathlib supplement ‚Äî the slice structure-sheaf ring map `œà_r` (Need #1 `hqc`)

The genuine wall of `hqc`: a single cross-ring slice structure-sheaf ring map `œà_r` from which the
colimit-preserving `SheafOfModules.pullback œà_r` is built.  For a scheme iso `œÜ : X ‚âÖ Y` and an open
`U·µ¢ ‚äÜ X` with image `V·µ¢ = œÜ.inv‚Åª¬π·µÅ U·µ¢ ‚äÜ Y`, the underlying opens-equivalence functor is
`F‚ÇÄ = Opens.map œÜ.inv.base : Opens X ‚•§ Opens Y` (sending `U·µ¢` to `V·µ¢` by `rfl`).  Its slice version
`Over.post F‚ÇÄ : Over U·µ¢ ‚•§ Over V·µ¢` is continuous and final (both because `F‚ÇÄ` is an equivalence,
`œÜ` being an iso).  The map `œà_r` is the slice of the structure-sheaf comparison
`œÜ.inv.toRingCatSheafHom : ùí™_X ‚ü∂ (F‚ÇÄ.sheafPushforwardContinuous _ _ _).obj ùí™_Y`, obtained simply by
applying the over-pullback functor `(Opens.grothendieckTopology X).overPullback RingCat U·µ¢`; the
codomain matches the desired sliced pushforward by the Beck‚ÄìChevalley identity
