open TopologicalSpace

variable {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (œÜ : X ‚âÖ Y) (Ui : X.Opens)

/-- `Opens.map œÜ.inv.base` is an equivalence (its base is the homeomorphism underlying `œÜ`).
Project-local instance feeding the continuity and finality of the slice functor `Over.post`. -/
instance opensMapInvBase_isEquivalence : (Opens.map œÜ.inv.base).IsEquivalence :=
  inferInstanceAs (Opens.mapMapIso (Scheme.forgetToTop.mapIso œÜ).symm).functor.IsEquivalence

/-- The slice functor `Over.post (Opens.map œÜ.inv.base) : Over U·µ¢ ‚•§ Over V·µ¢` is continuous for the
over-Grothendieck-topologies.  Project-local: from `coverPreserving_opens_map` lifted to the slices
